1777598910432588	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt5Qc		item.comment	bn-1rww	{"body":"Implementation landed in workspace bn-1rww (commit cca0b79).\n\nWhat works\n- `kb-query` gains `semantic-ort` feature (and a `kb-cli/semantic-ort` convenience feature). Default build is unchanged — no new deps pulled in.\n- New `MiniLmBackend` mirrors bones-search's ORT arm: model + tokenizer cached under `~/.cache/kb/models/`, auto-downloaded from Hugging Face on first use, `KB_SEMANTIC_AUTO_DOWNLOAD=0` opts out, override URLs via `KB_SEMANTIC_MODEL_URL` / `KB_SEMANTIC_TOKENIZER_URL`.\n- Runtime-dispatched `SemanticBackend` enum with `from_config` factory; `kb.toml [semantic]` selects the backend.\n- `kb compile`, `kb search`, `kb ask`, `kb serve` all build the same backend from config so corpus and query embeddings live in the same cosine space.\n- The pre-existing `handle_backend_change` truncate-on-id-flip pass continues to do the right thing — switching `backend = \"hash\" -> \"minilm\"` triggers a full re-embed on the next compile.\n- All 134 kb-query lib tests + 169 kb-cli tests pass under both feature configurations; clippy is clean for the crates I touched.\n\nAcceptance status\n- `cargo build --features semantic-ort` ✓\n- `kb compile` with `backend = \"minilm\"` produces 384-dim vectors ✓ (config plumbing + backend implementation; round-tripped TOML test confirms wiring)\n- \"≥+15% nDCG@10\" deferred to bn-hp3u — blocks on bn-3sco eval harness.\n- Falls back gracefully (clear error) when model file missing ✓ — same path as bones-search (`KB_SEMANTIC_AUTO_DOWNLOAD=0` short-circuit, missing-file error names the cache path).\n\nNotes for review\n- I did not add a network-dependent integration test for the auto-download path. The download logic is structurally identical to bones-search's; smoke-testing would either require a real HF round-trip (slow, flaky in CI) or a mock HTTP server (out of scope).\n- The `SemanticBackend` enum carries a `clippy::large_enum_variant` allow with a why-comment — only one is ever live per process and boxing would just add a heap hop.\n- Pre-existing clippy errors block `just check` on main itself; filed as bn-26cm so the bone-1rww commit isn't expanding scope."}	blake3:xoLPk1sovN2j9JzY8gRowHhHTKn_-if0HmV9YVSajB4
1777599623308832	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt5gc		item.move	bn-1rww	{"state":"done"}	blake3:LzmpFpcLW5hGGt5dCqyfqvgrZqy1XbYGttenEKEgN0I
1777600621741263	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt5wc		item.create	bn-2xbd	{"description":"**Why.** bn-1rww shipped MiniLM behind an opt-in `semantic-ort` feature; bones-cli unconditionally pulls in semantic-ort on non-Windows and falls back to model2vec on Windows so most users get the higher-quality backend by default. kb should match: MiniLM is the default on Linux/macOS, hash stays the default on Windows (we don't yet have model2vec).\n\n**What.**\n\n1. `crates/kb-cli/Cargo.toml`: move the `kb-query` dep into target-specific blocks — `cfg(not(windows))` enables `semantic-ort`, `cfg(windows)` keeps default features. Drop the workspace-level `semantic-ort` convenience feature now that the platform default does the work; keep `kb-query/semantic-ort` reachable for explicit `cargo build --features kb-query/semantic-ort` if anyone needs to force it on Windows.\n2. `crates/kb-query/src/semantic/model.rs`: switch `SemanticBackendKind`'s `#[default]` from `Hash` to `Minilm` on non-Windows via `cfg_attr`.\n3. `crates/kb-cli/src/config.rs`: same `cfg_attr` flip on `SemanticBackendKindConfig`.\n4. Adjust the `semantic_section_defaults_to_hash_backend` test to be platform-aware.\n\n**Risks.**\n- Existing kb installs upgrading on Linux/macOS will auto-download the ~22MB MiniLM model on first compile after upgrade. That's the bones behavior.\n- Integration tests rely on whatever backend the platform default selects; on a fresh CI machine they'll incur a one-time model download. Acceptable since this matches the bones flow and the model caches across runs.\n\nConfidence: 90% — straightforward Cargo + cfg_attr changes mirroring bones-cli.","kind":"task","title":"semantic: make MiniLM the default backend on non-Windows (mirror bones)"}	blake3:Y7f-oiYcuIwc3uFZDhn7MZBgjskehBCZwOl1ds2QsV8
