1777607855930839	kb-worker-2qda	itc:v3:AWLkyZOfkyeTkQAAAAAAQeta79a9dAAAAAEvAg		item.comment	bn-2qda	{"body":"Implemented in workspace bn-2qda (commit db272ca).\n\n## Files changed\n- `crates/kb-llm/src/adapter.rs` — new `LlmAdapter::caption_image(path, prompt)` trait method with default \"vision unsupported\" impl.\n- `crates/kb-llm/src/claude.rs` — implements `caption_image` (base64 data URI inline, mirrors `answer_question`).\n- `crates/kb-llm/src/opencode.rs` — implements `caption_image` (uses `-f <path>` attachment flag).\n- `crates/kb-compile/src/captions.rs` *(new, 738 lines incl. tests)* — the captions pass.\n- `crates/kb-compile/src/lib.rs` — pub mod captions.\n- `crates/kb-compile/src/pipeline.rs` — wires `captions` pass between backlinks and lexical_index, adds `CompileOptions.captions: CaptionsConfig`, helper `run_captions_pass`, dry-run preview entry, no-adapter Skipped entry.\n- `crates/kb-compile/tests/captions_integration.rs` *(new)* — end-to-end integration test through `run_compile_with_llm`.\n- `crates/kb-cli/src/config.rs` — new `CaptionsConfig` mirror under `CompileConfig`, with `to_pipeline_config()` translator and 3 round-trip tests.\n- `crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs` — `run_compile_action` plumbs `[compile.captions]` from the loaded `kb.toml` into `CompileOptions`.\n- `crates/kb-query/src/lexical.rs` — `index_source_page` now folds `caption-*` managed-region bodies into the indexed `summary` so caption text is searchable via `kb search`.\n\n## What's real vs stubbed\n\n**Real:**\n- The full compile pass: alt-text classification (empty / \"image\" / filename stem), allow_paths privacy gate, blake3 content-hash cache at `.kb/cache/captions/<hash>.txt`, managed-region injection, idempotent re-run.\n- `caption_image` on the **Claude adapter** — invokes `claude -p` with a base64 data URI for the image inline in the prompt. Mirrors the `answer_question` data-URI path that's already proven for Claude 4.X. Wires `--model haiku-4-5` (configurable via `kb.toml`).\n- `caption_image` on the **opencode adapter** — uses opencode's `-f <path>` attachment flag (already exposed by `opencode run --help`).\n- Lexical-index integration — caption text is now searchable.\n\n**Note on Claude vision wiring:** I went with the data-URI approach used by `answer_question` (bn-3dkw) rather than the bone's suggested `@<path>` shorthand. The `claude -p` CLI doesn't actually accept a `@<path>` shorthand for attachments — `--file` wants an Anthropic-uploaded `file_id`, not a local path — so the data-URI fallback is what actually works today. This is the **same trick `answer_question` already uses**, not a new stub.\n\n**Stubbed only in tests:** the unit tests use a tiny in-process `StubAdapter` (returns a fixed caption); the integration test uses a stub vision adapter that returns a canned caption to verify the pipeline. No real network calls in tests.\n\n## Sample compile invocation\n\n```toml\n# kb.toml\n[compile.captions]\nenabled = true\nrunner = \"claude\"\nmodel = \"claude-haiku-4-5\"\nallow_paths = [\"wiki/\", \"sources/\", \"raw/\"]\n```\n\nSource page `wiki/sources/example.md` body before:\n```markdown\n## Body\n\n![](diagram.png)\n```\n\nAfter `kb compile` (caption block injected; identical hash means no re-call on next compile):\n```markdown\n## Body\n\n![](diagram.png)\n<!-- kb:begin id=caption-3a2c…hash -->\nA diagram showing service A talking to service B over HTTP, with a Redis cache in between for session state.\n<!-- kb:end id=caption-3a2c…hash -->\n```\n\n`kb search \"service A\"` now returns the source page because `index_source_page` folds caption text into the indexed summary.\n\n## Test commands\n\n```bash\n# Unit tests for the captions module:\nmaw exec bn-2qda -- cargo test -p kb-compile --lib captions::\n\n# Integration test (full run_compile_with_llm with stub vision adapter):\nmaw exec bn-2qda -- cargo test -p kb-compile --test captions_integration\n\n# Config tests:\nmaw exec bn-2qda -- cargo test -p kb-cli config::\n\n# Full kb-compile + kb-llm + kb-query suites:\nmaw exec bn-2qda -- cargo test -p kb-compile -p kb-llm -p kb-query\n```\n\nAll pass: 204 lib + 1 captions integration + 3 concept_categories integration in kb-compile; 71 in kb-llm; 131 in kb-query; 169 in kb-cli.\n\n## Clippy\n\n`cargo clippy -p kb-compile -p kb-llm -p kb-cli --all-targets` is clean for the crates I touched. The remaining clippy errors all live in pre-existing files (`kb-core/state.rs:112`, `kb-lint/src/contradictions.rs:569`, `kb-lint/src/lib.rs:2622`) which are tracked under bn-26cm — none of them are in code I introduced.\n\n## Done-criteria checklist\n- [x] Wiki source with `![](diagram.png)` produces a kb:caption block after compile (verified by integration test).\n- [x] Re-running compile is a no-op for the captions pass (verified by integration test asserting `caption_call_count == 1` after two compiles).\n- [x] Tests pass for kb-compile + kb-cli.\n- [x] Clippy clean for the crates I touched (preexisting issues in kb-core/kb-lint excluded per bone direction)."}	blake3:5Ox2tLun7iJKqCZNvqJ_DG4nCVPzysZho1pZBemf39U
1777607884468193	kb-worker-3sco	itc:v3:AWKZnJJJyfySSSUAAAAAQbbqq6_qqqAAAAEzAg		item.comment	bn-3sco	{"body":"Done in workspace bn-3sco.\n\nFiles added:\n- crates/kb-cli/src/eval/mod.rs        — CLI dispatch + RunFlags\n- crates/kb-cli/src/eval/scoring.rs    — pure metrics: precision_at_k, mean_reciprocal_rank, ndcg_at_k (+ unit tests)\n- crates/kb-cli/src/eval/golden.rs     — golden.toml loader/validator (+ unit tests)\n- crates/kb-cli/src/eval/runner.rs     — drives queries through plan_retrieval_hybrid_with_backend, JSON+md writers, baseline diff (+ unit tests)\n- crates/kb-cli/src/eval/golden.toml.example — bootstrap template, 4 sample queries\n- crates/kb-cli/src/eval/README.md     — short docs (metrics, layout, corpus pinning)\nFiles modified:\n- crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs            — added `mod eval;`, Command::Eval { action }, EvalAction::{Run, List}, dispatch\n- crates/kb-cli/tests/integration_tests.rs — bn-3sco end-to-end test\n\nSubcommands shipped:\n  kb eval run                      # writes evals/results/<UTC-ts>.json + latest.md\n  kb eval run --save-as <name>     # additional copy at evals/results/<name>.json\n  kb eval run --baseline <name>    # side-by-side diff table; warns on corpus_hash drift\n  kb eval list                     # newest-first listing of evals/results/*.json\n\nSample CLI invocation against a 2-source demo kb (auth + billing):\n\n  kb eval run\n  > kb eval run: 2 queries — P@5 0.200, P@10 0.100, MRR 1.000, nDCG@10 1.000\n  >   result: <root>/evals/results/2026-05-01T03-56-31Z.json\n  >   latest.md: <root>/evals/results/latest.md\n\nJSON shape includes run_id, corpus_hash (BLAKE3 of state/indexes/lexical.json), backend_id (e.g. ort-minilm-384), per-query {p_at_5, p_at_10, mrr, ndcg_10, ranking, relevant_hits}, and aggregate.\n\nTests for the lead to run:\n  maw exec bn-3sco -- cargo test -p kb-cli --bin kb eval::      # 30 unit tests (scoring/golden/runner)\n  maw exec bn-3sco -- cargo test -p kb-cli --test integration_tests eval_run_writes_json_and_markdown_with_finite_metrics\n  maw exec bn-3sco -- cargo test -p kb-cli                      # full kb-cli suite (170 pass)\n  maw exec bn-3sco -- cargo clippy -p kb-cli --all-targets --no-deps   # clean (kb-cli only — bn-26cm clippy errors live in kb-lint/kb-core/kb-ingest, not kb-cli)\n\nHonest notes:\n- Wrote a small Howard-Hinnant-style civil-from-days routine to format the run_id timestamp without pulling in chrono. Covered with two unit tests (epoch-zero + a known mid-2024 instant).\n- The integration test uses the existing `write_paraphrase_fixture` (src-cred / src-billing / src-frontend) so it exercises the same hybrid path as the bn-3qsj search tests. P@5 = 0.2 in the demo because the corpus is intentionally tiny (1 of 5 candidates is the expected source) — meaningful values come once a real kb has dozens of candidates per query.\n- `cargo clippy -p kb-cli --all-targets` (default, with deps) trips on the three pre-existing kb-lint/kb-core/kb-ingest errors tracked as bn-26cm. `--no-deps` (which the lead recommended in the brief) is clean.\n- DID NOT merge. Workspace bn-3sco is ready for review."}	blake3:ExcjUgijxoDR_w53NXmQ9_UPFGUf_inJ6R6EzCvYmRk
1777608092752677	kb-worker-3rzz	itc:v3:AWL-ck5ySTySSUAAAAAAQf7q7qr1VQAAAAEwAg		item.comment	bn-3rzz	{"body":"Done in workspace bn-3rzz (commit 3c78c2c). Files changed:\n\n- new crates/kb-query/src/semantic/chunk.rs — pure chunker (chunk_markdown, Chunk struct), 11 unit tests\n- crates/kb-query/src/semantic/embed.rs — schema swap to chunk_embeddings(chunk_id PRIMARY KEY, item_id, chunk_idx, heading, content_hash, embedding_json) + idx_chunk_item; rewritten sync_embeddings to walk per-chunk; per-chunk hash dedup; stale cleanup deletes rows whose item is gone OR whose chunk_idx exceeds current count; ensure_embedding_schema now drops legacy item_embeddings\n- crates/kb-query/src/semantic/model.rs — backend ids bumped to hash-embed-256-chunked / ort-minilm-384-chunked so existing kbs auto re-embed via handle_backend_change\n- crates/kb-query/src/semantic/search.rs — SemanticSearchResult now carries chunk_id + chunk_idx + heading; new SemanticChunkHit alias; new aggregate_chunks_to_items collapses chunks to items by max-chunk-score with best_chunk attached\n- crates/kb-query/src/hybrid.rs — run_semantic over-scans chunks (4x) then aggregates; existing fusion math unchanged\n- crates/kb-query/src/{mod.rs,lib.rs} — re-exports for chunk_markdown, SemanticChunkHit, SemanticItemHit, aggregate_chunks_to_items, knn_search, chunk_id_for\n- crates/kb-cli/src/forget.rs — DELETE FROM chunk_embeddings (was item_embeddings)\n- crates/kb-cli/tests/integration_tests.rs — updated forget test to chunk_embeddings; added two new tests:\n  - multi_section_source_produces_multiple_chunk_embeddings (verifies multiple rows + heading metadata)\n  - search_finds_source_via_non_first_section_chunk (verifies the second-section chunk outranks the first when query matches)\n- crates/kb-core/src/citation_verify.rs — QuoteCitation gained section_anchor: Option<String>; the bracket-form regexes now optionally capture a #section-slug suffix; new resolve_section_anchor() helper compares anchor against slugified on-disk headings; dedup key includes anchor; 6 new tests cover both forms + dedup + anchor resolution + fallback\n- crates/kb-core/src/lib.rs — re-export resolve_section_anchor\n\nIn scope:\n- Per-chunk schema + pipeline + retrieval\n- Citation parser recognizes [src-id#section-name]; resolver helper for renderers; existing [src-id] form unchanged\n- Tests across kb-query (chunker + embed + search), kb-core (citation parser), and kb-cli (multi-section + non-first-section retrieval integration)\n\nOut of scope (and why):\n- LLM prompts: no existing prompt emits [src-id] markers (kb ask uses numeric [N] manifest form; concept_body / summarize_document don't cite at all). Nothing to update.\n- artifact.rs CitationManifest: that flow is for the [N] manifest, orthogonal to [src-id#section] surfaces. Anchor-aware rendering for the [N] form already exists.\n- Eval harness nDCG: depends on bn for eval harness; that bone is the gating dependency the description listed.\n\nKnown issues / compromises:\n- Chunker's heading text uses the H2/H3 raw text (after trim, trailing-hash strip) — no anchor slug stored alongside. Renderers must slugify via slug_from_title to match the section_anchor parser produces. resolve_section_anchor() does this; documented in its rustdoc.\n- Concept pages typically have no H2 → single chunk with heading: None. Embedding input prepends title + aliases as a \"lead\" so retrieval still works. Same shape as the old whole-page approach for these.\n- The QUOTE_THEN_PAREN_RE form (\"text\" (src-id)) does NOT carry an anchor. Agents tend to use the bracket forms when pointing at a section; keeping paren bare avoids ambiguous matches against e.g. (src-id) \"...\" (different stuff).\n\nTest commands the lead should run:\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo test -p kb-query\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo test -p kb-query --features semantic-ort\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo test -p kb-core\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo test -p kb-cli --tests\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo test -p kb-cli --tests --features kb-cli/semantic-ort\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo test -p kb-compile\n\n  # Clippy clean for kb-query and kb-core (touched crates):\n  maw exec bn-3rzz -- cargo clippy -p kb-query -p kb-core --all-targets --features kb-query/semantic-ort\n\n(kb-lint clippy still trips on the pre-existing bn-26cm error at contradictions.rs:569 — out of scope.)\n\nFinal test counts: kb-query 152, kb-core 90 + 4, kb-cli 171 (was 169; added 2), kb-compile 186 + 3, all passing."}	blake3:cTvGwhqtDFgb3RJeZdmNEQBhtORY8ytlEyZ45v443Vw
