1777657878030903	kb-worker-32od	itc:v3:AWKTyZJJJMnMk50AAAAAQa9aqq12ruAAAAEzAg		item.comment	bn-32od	{"body":"Done.\n\nWorkspace: bn-32od\n\nFiles changed:\n- crates/kb-query/src/structural/mod.rs (new — `StructuralScorer`, `StructuralOptions`)\n- crates/kb-query/src/structural/graph.rs (new — graph build/persist/load on `.kb/state/graph.db`)\n- crates/kb-query/src/structural/pagerank.rs (new — personalized PageRank power-iteration)\n- crates/kb-query/src/lib.rs (re-export structural surface)\n- crates/kb-query/src/lexical.rs (added `structural_score` / `structural_rank` to `RetrievalCandidate`)\n- crates/kb-query/src/hybrid.rs (added structural tier to fuse + plan flow, `KB_STRUCTURAL` env, `StructuralHit`, `with_structural` helper, fields on `HybridResult`)\n- crates/kb-compile/src/pipeline.rs (added `structural_index` pass between `index_pages` and `embedding_sync`, dry-run + live)\n- crates/kb-cli/src/config.rs (new `[semantic.structural]` section + threading into `to_hybrid_options`)\n- crates/kb-cli/tests/integration_tests.rs (new `structural_tier_boosts_multi_cited_source` integration test)\n\nSample `kb search structural --json` (3-source/2-concept fixture; src-shared cited by both concepts, src-orphan cited by neither):\n\n  src-shared    score=0.0487  reasons=[lexical(rank 2), semantic(rank 2 score 0.50), structural match (rank 1, score 0.57)]\n  src-orphan    score=0.0328  reasons=[lexical(rank 1), semantic(rank 1 score 0.69)]                        # no structural reason\n  alpha concept score=0.0315  reasons=[semantic(rank 5), structural match (rank 2, score 0.21)]\n  beta  concept score=0.0315  reasons=[semantic(rank 4), structural match (rank 3, score 0.21)]\n\nSame query with `KB_STRUCTURAL=0` flips back to lex+sem-only ranking — src-orphan moves to position 1 because it has slightly higher lexical+semantic score, and no result carries a `structural match` reason. Identical fallback to pre-bone behavior.\n\nTest commands the lead should run:\n- `maw exec bn-32od -- cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` (verified clean)\n- `maw exec bn-32od -- cargo test --workspace` (verified — 183 integration tests + all unit tests pass; 16 new unit tests in structural::*)\n- `maw exec bn-32od -- cargo test --test integration_tests structural_tier_boosts_multi_cited_source` (focused on the new fixture)\n\nNotes:\n- Did NOT add petgraph to the workspace as the bone hinted — it isn't there yet, and the PPR loop is small enough (sub-200 lines) that pulling in a graph crate would have been more weight than warranted. Used a contiguous-index adjacency list directly. If you want petgraph later for future expansion, the swap is contained inside `pagerank.rs`.\n- Edges dedupe `cites` and `links` between the same pair when loaded — for PPR it's the connection that matters, not which kind. Stored separately on disk so `kb inspect` could surface them later.\n- Index pages (`wiki/*/index.md`) are skipped at build time so they don't dominate teleport.\n- Dangling-mass redistribution is the standard patch (otherwise mass would leak each iteration).\n- `KB_STRUCTURAL=0` mirrors `KB_SEMANTIC=0` for kill-switch parity.\n\nDid NOT push or merge — leaving that to the lead."}	blake3:SkQbZOSGbyki5tWE9TW3z5XqYzEIuz-pWjr50GuQ0jY
